	<li><p>Find the slope of the linear function <m>g(w)</m> that relates <m>g</m> to <m>w</m>.</p></li>
	<li><p>Write the equation of the linear function <m>g(w)</m> that relates <m>g</m> to <m>w</m>.</p></li>
	<li><p>What is the expected percent seed germination for a minimum winter temperature of <m>30.5^\circ\text{F}</m>?</p></li>
	<li><p>Suppose you found 25% seed germination, what is the corresponding minimum winter temperature?</p></li>

		</ol></p>

		<p>
			Before we leave this topic, let’s look at these formulas in some extreme situations and figure out how they are connected. This will hopefully give us confidence with a less familiar-looking formula as well as give us some reasoning tools for how graphs and formulas are connected.
		</p>

